<% provide :page_title, 'Details' %>

<div class="container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col">
      <div class="card mt-5 mb-5 details-page">
        <div class="row">
          <div class="col">
            <h1 class="text-center header">Factorio Helper Details</h1>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row mt-5">
          <div class="col-sm-10 offset-sm-1 col-md-8 offset-md-2 col-lg-6 offset-lg-3">
            <h4 class="text-center">File upload format</h4>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-4">
              <p>In order for the upload process to work, the file you chose to upload
              must conform to the folowing format:</p>
            </div>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-4">
              <pre>
{
  "recipes": [
    {
        "name": "Recipe Name",
        "inputs":
        {
            "Input Name": input-amount,
            etc...
        },
        "outputs":
        {
            "Output Name": output-amount,
            etc...
        },
        "energy": production-time
    },
    etc...
  ]
}
              </pre>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="row mt-5">
          <div class="col-sm-10 offset-sm-1 col-md-8 offset-md-2 col-lg-6 offset-lg-3">
            <h4 class="text-center">Data Exporter Mod</h4>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-4">
              <p>To make getting the recipe data from your game, use the Data Exporter mod. This mod adds the "/export" console command, which will generate a JSON file for you. This mod can be found on the Factorio mod portal, or you can download the mod here.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="d-flex justify-content-center mt-2">
              <%= link_to 'Download', root_url << '/data-exporter_0.1.0.zip', class: 'btn btn-outline-primary round mb-4' %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
